column1:
• All of your answers should be typed or pasted into the grey boxes. 

• Questions with grey answer boxes expect a specific answer. If you input the correct answer, the question number box  will change from blue to green.

• Questions with yellow answer boxes are free response questions. There will be no change in the question number boxes (in blue), regardless of answer.

• For hints for each question, hover your mouse over the blue hint box to get helpful information!

column2: In the Month column, extract the month from each date.
In the DayOfWeek column, extract the day of the week from each date. Hint: It will make it easier later in the Miestone if you have Monday = 1 , Sunday = 7.

column1: In the YellowLine column, we want to capture whether or not a station is on the Yellow Line. To create this feature, we'll do it in two steps.

column2: In the FirstLetter column, extract the first letter from the Lines column. e.g. "YO" should output "Y".

Then, in the YellowLine column, extract whether or not a station is on the Yellow Line: "Yes" if it is on the Yellow Line, and "No" if it is not. Hint: Based on the Data Dictionary, a station is on the Yellow line if the first letter of the Lines string is a Y.

column1: Use the engineered columns to answer the following questions.

column2: What is the total number of passengers who rode the BART in all of 2021?
How many rows of data are there?
How many total passengers rode during a weekday?
How many passengers rode on the Yellow Line?
What proportion of all passengers ended on a station on the Yellow Line?

LevelUp (Optional): In the Downtown column, extract whether or not a station is one of the four stations in downtown San Francisco: EM, MT, PL, CC: "Yes" if it is one of those stations, "No" if it is not.
